<br>
At 53 - 5 Dryads for 2% XP (half a blue)<br>
At 54 - 7 Dryads for 2%<br>
At 55 - 10 Dryads for 2%<br>
At 56 - 12 Dryads for 2% (yes, Dryads are light blue)<br>
<br>
Dryads are on an 8:30 timer from death. With KEI and horse, Air, Plate, two Daggers of Symbols, Elemental Blanket (both for MR), BO3, and Shield of Lava, I was able to comfortably kill 6 to 8 in 10 minutes from 53 through 55. At 56, not using Plate seems to make little difference, as with Muzzle, Daggers, Blanket, BO3, and CoF my pet eats them up and about 8 per 10 minutes looks possible. Without KEI, drop two or three per 10 minutes from the counts, if careful with casting. Without horse? Why are you without horse?? YMMV...<br>
<br>
Key seems to be timing on keeping the Dryad out of heal mode (below 40%) and getting her into flee mode (below 20%). SFAIK, Dryads have about 3200 HP (Sirocco 630 DMG waves are about 20% HP each). For Lava Bolt / Char users, that probably means hitting with the second cast just below 40% (700 DMG is about 20%). For Sirocco users I'd suggest just below 80% (3 waves at 20% each is 60%) and whacking with Char if pet doesn't do a solid job if a wave or more is resisted.<br>
<br>
I keep Char memmed as working the spawns with the wanderers sometimes needs something more precise than Sirocco to keep from aggro-ing a wanderer.<br>
<br>
As for wanderers, one kill gave me worst-possible faction. No faction on the griffs. I have probably killed about 20 &quot;good&quot; animals and am still amiable in the town, though have done a few gnoll trips as well.<br>
<br>
GL - you may still see me there as I get that one-yellow &quot;death buffer&quot; before moving on...<br>
<br>
Itchyban<br>
